18.20	Ice_hockey_at_the_2006_Winter_Olympics	Ice hockey at the 2006 Winter Olympics	Ice hockey at the 2006 Winter Olympics was held at the Torino Palasport Olimpico and the Torino Esposizioni in Turin, Italy. The men's competition, held from 15 to 26 February, was won by Sweden, and the women's competition, held from 11 to 20 February, was won by Canada.	
